# Compliance Rules (Wolverhampton PHV Operator)

## Booking Records

- Store: pickup/dropoff, times, passenger contact, vehicle, driver, fare, status history.
- `booking_status_history` append-only — never mutate past rows.
- `dispatch_logs` for every assignment/reassignment.

## Licences

- Track PHV driver licence, PHV vehicle licence, DVLA driving licence.
- Block dispatch if licence expired or missing (`COMPLIANCE_BLOCKED` error).
- Alert when `EXPIRING_SOON` (30 days).

## Complaints & Safeguarding

- Unique references: `CMP-*`, `SG-*`.
- Safeguarding HIGH/CRITICAL triggers immediate audit log + operator notification.
- Retain complaint/safeguarding records per operator retention policy.

## Data Protection (UK GDPR)

- Lawful basis: contract + legal obligation for licensing records.
- Support data export and erasure requests (anonymize bookings past retention only).
- Encrypt data at rest (RDS) and in transit (TLS).

## Reporting

- Admin can export audit logs and booking registers for council inspections.
- Reports must include operator licence number in header metadata.
